 # SAVI Change Log - 2026-05-05
 
+## Sample Library V22 Screenshot Warranty And Folder Intelligence
+
+- Created rollback archive:
+  `Docs/Design/SampleLibraryArchive/2026-05-05-before-v22-screenshot-warranty-folder-intelligence/`.
+- Bumped native sample seed version to `22`.
+- Added `A/C warranty screenshot`, a generated iPhone-style screenshot sample in
+  `Life Admin` with warranty, appliance, serial-number, receipt, and screenshot
+  tags.
+- Strengthened Mom's lasagna voice note as an audio-tagged file sample with
+  `audio/mp4` metadata so Search/refine can demonstrate audio filtering.
+- Hardened shared folder classification:
+  - warranty/serial/model-number, booking-confirmation, door/Wi-Fi code, and
+    practical admin screenshots now prefer `Life Admin`;
+  - driver licenses, passports, insurance cards, banking/routing, tax, medical,
+    credentials, and private IDs still prefer `Private Vault`;
+  - hotel confirmations no longer get forced into Places just because they say
+    `hotel`.
+- Added deterministic classifier audit cases for warranty screenshots, hotel
+  confirmations, and private ID screenshots.
+- Added short Vision OCR enrichment for image shares in the share extension, so
+  screenshots can improve title, tags, and folder choice after the first fast
+  render without requiring Apple Intelligence.
+- Improved share-sheet smart folder copy so users see `Smart folder` plus a
+  plain-English reason like `codes, warranty, or docs`.
+- Expanded smart tag defaults for warranty, booking confirmations, serial
+  numbers, audio/voice notes, and local document/file extensions.
+- Release iPhoneOS no-sign build passed after V22:
+  `/Users/guest1/Desktop/SAVI_QA/testflight-final-prep-20260505-003401/release-iphoneos-nosign-build-v22-folder-intelligence.log`.
+- Captured a focused Release Home screenshot on the healthy iPhone 17 Pro
+  simulator after a fresh install:
+  `/Users/guest1/Desktop/SAVI_QA/savi-v22-home-iphone17pro-release-20260505-102752.png`.
+- Attempted a focused iPhone SE simulator Home pass twice; both runs hung in
+  CoreSimulator before reliable app screenshot capture, including one fresh
+  recreated SE device stuck around boot/terminate. This was recorded as simulator
+  infrastructure friction, not a Release build failure.
+
